{
  "total_duration": 506.96,
  "lines": [
    {
      "i": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 12.76,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "想象你和同学约好：他今天忘带笔，先向你借一支，明天还回来。这件事能顺利，是因为方向很清楚：谁借走了，什么时候还回来。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 1,
      "start": 13.11,
      "end": 35.477,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的题目是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "One good turn deserves another"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，中文可以说“礼尚往来”。这里的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "turn"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "不是转弯，而是一个 kind act，一个好心的帮忙；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "deserve"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“按道理应该得到”。别人帮了你一次，你也应该公平地回报。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 2,
      "start": 35.827,
      "end": 51.987,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "可是课文里的托尼·斯蒂尔把这句话用歪了。他不是在讲真正的公平，而是把“你帮我、我帮你”变成“你替我付饭钱”。所以这一课的核心不是餐厅，而是借、还、人情和账单的方向。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 3,
      "start": 52.337,
      "end": 69.993,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "故事一开始，叙述者正在餐厅吃饭："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I was having dinner at a restaurant when Tony Steele came in."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "背景动作是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "was having dinner"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，这时托尼进来了。一个普通饭局，马上要变成一场关于借钱的小游戏。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 4,
      "start": 70.343,
      "end": 91.55,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文接着给托尼补背景："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Tony worked in a lawyer's office years ago, but he is now working at a bank."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "他以前在律师事务所工作，现在在银行工作。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He gets a good salary"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，他薪水不错，所以后面的借钱不是因为课文说他没有收入，而是因为他习惯占朋友便宜。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "start": 91.9,
      "end": 110.02,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "托尼的问题很清楚："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "he always borrows money from his friends and never pays it back."
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow from"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是从别人那里借进来，钱来到他这边；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay it back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是把借来的钱还回去。托尼常常只做前半步，不做后半步。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 6,
      "start": 110.37,
      "end": 138.609,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这一次，叙述者反过来问托尼："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "While he was eating, I asked him to lend me twenty pounds."
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend me"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是托尼把钱借给我。出人意料的是，托尼立刻给了钱："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "To my surprise, he gave me the money immediately."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "然后他说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "so now you can pay for my dinner!"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "他给钱很快，可是已经把这笔钱变成了别人替他付的饭钱。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 7,
      "start": 138.959,
      "end": 146.519,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这一课最先要听懂题目："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "One good turn deserves another"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。它本来是什么意思？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 8,
      "start": 146.869,
      "end": 150.038,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是不是别人帮我一次，我也应该回一个好意？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 9,
      "start": 150.388,
      "end": 161.348,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对，这叫公平的礼尚往来。比如同学借你的橡皮，按时还回来；你今天帮他递作业，他明天也愿意帮你一个小忙。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 10,
      "start": 161.698,
      "end": 167.981,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那托尼也算做了一个"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "good turn"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "吗？他马上给了钱。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 11,
      "start": 168.331,
      "end": 178.451,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "表面上像。可是他马上加了一句：现在你可以替我付晚饭钱。这样一来，他不是在还人情，而是在制造新账单。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 12,
      "start": 178.801,
      "end": 181.636,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以他把谚语扭成了自己的理由？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 13,
      "start": 181.986,
      "end": 197.449,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "正是。真正的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "要有 return，借了要还；真正的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "good turn"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "也不能变成陷阱。托尼的问题，是把人情、借钱和饭钱混在一起，让别人吃亏。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 14,
      "start": 197.799,
      "end": 203.898,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "和"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "我总是分不清。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 15,
      "start": 204.247,
      "end": 229.015,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "看钱或东西的方向就行。钱来到我这里，我"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow money from Tony"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。钱从我这里出去给别人，我"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend Tony money"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "或"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend money to Tony"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。借来的钱回去，叫"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay it back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。替某个东西付款，比如晚餐，叫"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay for dinner"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 16,
      "start": 229.365,
      "end": 233.244,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "twenty pounds"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "呢？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 17,
      "start": 233.594,
      "end": 250.825,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "它是故事里的英国钱数，我们只要知道这是一笔吃饭时借的钱，不需要换算。重点是：托尼在银行工作，有不错的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "salary"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，却总向朋友借钱不还。最后他“立刻”给钱，反而让笑点更讽刺。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 18,
      "start": 251.175,
      "end": 255.183,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I was having dinner at a restaurant when Tony Steele came in."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 19,
      "start": 255.533,
      "end": 260.501,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Tony worked in a lawyer's office years ago, but he is now working at a bank."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 20,
      "start": 260.851,
      "end": 266.347,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He gets a good salary, but he always borrows money from his friends and never pays it back."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 21,
      "start": 266.697,
      "end": 270.129,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Tony saw me and came and sat at the same table."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 22,
      "start": 270.479,
      "end": 273.311,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He has never borrowed money from me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 23,
      "start": 273.661,
      "end": 277.549,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "While he was eating, I asked him to lend me twenty pounds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 24,
      "start": 277.898,
      "end": 281.498,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "To my surprise, he gave me the money immediately."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 25,
      "start": 281.848,
      "end": 287.248,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'I have never borrowed any money from you,' Tony said, 'so now you can pay for my dinner!'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 26,
      "start": 287.598,
      "end": 290.166,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "borrow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第一个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 27,
      "start": 290.516,
      "end": 292.052,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "borrow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 28,
      "start": 292.402,
      "end": 316.853,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "borrow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“借入”，方向是东西来到我这里，所以常用"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow from"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。比如"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I borrow money from Tony."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "钱从托尼那里来到我这里。课文里托尼总是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrows money from his friends"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，问题是他"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "never pays it back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，从来不还。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 29,
      "start": 317.203,
      "end": 319.811,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lend"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 30,
      "start": 320.161,
      "end": 321.697,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lend"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 31,
      "start": 322.047,
      "end": 342.73,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lend"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lend"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“借出”，方向是东西从我这里出去给别人。比如"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Tony lends me money."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "或者"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Tony lends money to me."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文里叙述者说"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I asked him to lend me twenty pounds"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，就是请托尼把二十英镑借给我。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 32,
      "start": 343.08,
      "end": 346.128,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "pay"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三个短语："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 33,
      "start": 346.478,
      "end": 348.134,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "pay"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 34,
      "start": 348.484,
      "end": 374.387,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "pay"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“还钱”。借东西可以是小事，比如铅笔、橡皮、充电器；借钱更要谨慎，孩子不能随便处理大额借贷。但公平规则一样：如果你"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "borrow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，就应该"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay it back"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。另外"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "pay for dinner"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“为晚餐付款”，不是“还钱”，这里正是托尼偷换方向的地方。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 35,
      "start": 374.737,
      "end": 428.38,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的 grammar 不用做成时态表，我们看场景怎么推动笑点。第一层是背景动作："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I was having dinner at a restaurant"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，我正在吃饭；突然事件是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "when Tony Steele came in"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，托尼进来了。第二层是人物背景："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "worked in a lawyer's office years ago"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是过去的工作，"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "is now working at a bank"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是现在的工作，"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "gets a good salary"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "说明他并不是没收入。第三层是借钱历史："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He has never borrowed money from me"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，到现在为止他从没向我借过钱。这句话让结尾成立：托尼说既然他以前没向我借过，那现在我就可以替他付饭钱。语法服务于这个小讽刺：当时桌上发生什么，托尼平时怎么做，他和叙述者之间又缺了哪一笔旧账。"
